:"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude's context window architecture provides "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"industry-leading capacity"},{"type":"text","text":" with standard 200K tokens (150K words, 500 pages) and premium 1M tokens (750K words, 2,500 pages) for enterprise Opus and Sonnet deployments. All Claude 4.5 models share a unified 200K buffer by default, with 1M access unlocked via premium/enterprise tiers and usage credits. The window is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"shared, unified buffer"},{"type":"text","text":" where input and output both count toward the same limit, but output has a separate maximum constraint (64K tokens per response for 4.5 models). For production workloads, recommended usage is 20K–80K tokens per request to maintain optimal latency and output clarity, and automatic context management (when code execution is enabled) can summarize earlier messages to allow indefinite conversations within the limit."}]}]}}
